    {
      "id": "sybil_2_listing_2",
      "firm_id": "sybil_2",
      "description": "Offering a mechanically sorted 2004 BMW M3 (E46) featuring the high-revving S54B32 power plant. This 3.2L inline-six utilizes individual throttle bodies and dual-VANOS variable valve timing to deliver a visceral 8,000 RPM redline. Power is sent to the rear wheels via a Getrag 6-speed manual gearbox and a factory-spec M-Variable limited-slip differential. The chassis has been enhanced with reinforced rear subframe mounting points and refreshed suspension bushings to maintain optimal toe and camber curves under load. Recent preventative maintenance includes a VANOS overhaul and valve clearance adjustment. While the finish exhibits minor patina consistent with a well-loved enthusiast vehicle, the powertrain remains tight with linear torque delivery and crisp throttle response. A quintessential driver's specification for those who prioritize analog feedback and mechanical integrity.",
